==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Appointee
<hw>Ap*point*ee"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>appoint⟦eacute⟧</ets>, p. p. of <ets>appointer</ets>. See
<er>Appoint</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A person
appointed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The commission authorizes them to make appointments, and pay the
<qex>appointees</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Circular of Mass. Representatives
(1768).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(law)</fld> <def>A person in whose favor a power of
appointment is executed.</def> <rj><au>Kent. Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Appointer</ent>⟦br⟧
